=====
Quick C/C++ String Benchmark.
=====

The third-party and cmake directories contains (awesome) work 
from Paul Hsieh, Maxim Yegorushkin and Joshua L. Blocher.

In the simplest case(s), requires just a C++ compiler:

    $ c++ string-cat.cpp -DUSE_STD_STRING -o cat-std-string
    $ ./benchmark.pl README

For a complete support, you will need:
- g++
- make
- cmake
- Perl + Data::Dumper
- Python libraries
- Boehm Garbage Collector + Cord
- Qt4
- GNU time
- md5sum
- chrt

Then, if you're feeling (very) lucky, you can:

    $ mkdir build
    $ cd build
    $ cmake ..
    $ make -j4
    $ cd ..
    $ perl benchmark.pl README --path=build --verbose > results.pm

This yields human-readable Perl modules, for alternative output (YAML/JSON/XML):

    $ perl -MYAML -e'print Dump do "results.pm"'
    $ perl -MJSON -e'print to_json do "results.pm"'
    $ perl -MXML::Simple -e'print XMLout do "results.pm"'

